iotop is a top-like utility that monitors system '''i'''nput/'''o'''utput.

__TOC__

== Installation ==
=== Kernel ===
The <code>CONFIG_TASK_IO_ACCOUNTING</code> variable must be enabled in the Linux kernel for the <tt>iotop</tt> command to work properly. It can be found at this location:

{{KernelBox|title=Kernel configuration for iotop|1=<pre>
General setup
-> CPU/Task time and stats accounting
   [*] Enable extended accounting over taskstats
   [*] Enable per-task storage I/O accounting
</pre>}}

